===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''[in]fu(n)do''  ''fu(n)dere''  ''fusi''  ''fusum'': to pour.
===Noun===
'''infusion'''
# That which is [[infuse]]d. This is the most common meaning.
#* An extract of [[rooibos]] and [[chamomile]] makes a refreshing '''infusion'''.
# The act of [[steep]]ing or [[soak]]ing a substance in liquid so as to extract [[medicinal]] or [[herbal]] qualities.
# The act of installing a quality into a person.
# (obsolete) The act of dipping into a fluid.

